<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREF.5B.5BErnst_Haeckel.7CHaeckel.2C_Ernst.5D.5D1876"><a href="/wiki/Ernst_Haeckel" title="Ernst Haeckel">Haeckel, Ernst</a> (1876). <a href="http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/Radical%20Ecology.htm#EUGENICS%20JUSTIFIED%20BY%20NATURE" class="external text" title="http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/Radical%20Ecology.htm#EUGENICS%20JUSTIFIED%20BY%20NATURE" rel="nofollow">"The History of Creation, vol. I"</a>. New York: D. Appleton. pp. 170<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/Radical%20Ecology.htm#EUGENICS%20JUSTIFIED%20BY%20NATURE" class="external free" title="http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/Radical%20Ecology.htm#EUGENICS%20JUSTIFIED%20BY%20NATURE" rel="nofollow">http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/Radical%20Ecology.htm#EUGENICS%20JUSTIFIED%20BY%20NATURE</a></span>.  "Among the Spartans all newly born children were subject to a careful examination or selection. All those that were weak, sickly, or affected with any bodily infirmity, were killed. Only the perfectly healthy and strong children were allowed to live, and they alone afterwards propagated the race."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+History+of+Creation%2C+vol.+I&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BErnst+Haeckel%7CHaeckel%2C+Ernst%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BErnst+Haeckel%7CHaeckel%2C+Ernst%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1876&amp;rft.pages=pp.+170&amp;rft.pub=New+York%3A+D.+Appleton&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldfuturefund.org%2Fwffmaster%2FReading%2FGermany%2FRadical%2520Ecology.htm%23EUGENICS%2520JUSTIFIED%2520BY%2520NATURE&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Eugenics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BAdolf_Hitler.7CHitler.2C_Adolf.5D.5D1961"><a href="/wiki/Adolf_Hitler" title="Adolf Hitler">Hitler, Adolf</a> (1961). <i><a href="/wiki/Hitler%27s_Secret_Book" title="Hitler's Secret Book" class="mw-redirect">Hitler's Secret Book</a></i>. New York: Grove Press. pp.&#160;8–9, 17–18. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0394620038" class="internal">ISBN 0394620038</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/9830111" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/9830111" rel="nofollow">9830111</a>.  "At one time the Spartans were capable of such a wise measure, but not our present, mendaciously sentimental, bourgeois patriotic nonsense. The rule of six thousand Spartans over three hundred and fifty thousand Helots was only thinkable in consequence of the high racial value of the Spartans. But this was the result of a systematic race preservation; thus Sparta must be regarded as the first Völkisch State. The exposure of the sick, weak, deformed children, in short, their destruction, was more decent and in truth a thousand times more humane than the wretched insanity of our day which preserves the most pathological subject, and indeed at any price, and yet takes the life of a hundred thousand healthy children in consequence of birth control or through abortions, in order subsequently to breed a race of degenerates burdened with illnesses."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BHitler%27s+Secret+Book%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BAdolf+Hitler%7CHitler%2C+Adolf%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BAdolf+Hitler%7CHitler%2C+Adolf%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1961&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B8%E2%80%939%2C+17%E2%80%9318&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Grove+Press&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/9830111&amp;rft.isbn=0394620038&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Eugenics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHawkins.2C_Mike1997">Hawkins, Mike (1997). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=SszNCxSKmgkC&amp;pg=PA276&amp;dq=Hitler%27s+Secret+Book+sparta&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=q5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s#PPA276,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=SszNCxSKmgkC&amp;pg=PA276&amp;dq=Hitler%27s+Secret+Book+sparta&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=q5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s#PPA276,M1" rel="nofollow">Social Darwinism in European and American Thought, 1860-1945: nature as model and nature as threat</a></i>. Cambridge University Press. pp.&#160;276. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/052157434X" class="internal">ISBN 052157434X</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/34705047" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/34705047" rel="nofollow">34705047</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=SszNCxSKmgkC&amp;pg=PA276&amp;dq=Hitler%27s+Secret+Book+sparta&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=q5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s#PPA276,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=SszNCxSKmgkC&amp;pg=PA276&amp;dq=Hitler%27s+Secret+Book+sparta&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=q5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s#PPA276,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=SszNCxSKmgkC&amp;pg=PA276&amp;dq=Hitler%27s+Secret+Book+sparta&amp;ie=ISO-8859-1&amp;sig=q5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s#PPA276,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Social+Darwinism+in+European+and+American+Thought%2C+1860-1945%3A+nature+as+model+and+nature+as+threat&amp;rft.aulast=Hawkins%2C+Mike&amp;rft.au=Hawkins%2C+Mike&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B276&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/34705047&amp;rft.isbn=052157434X&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DSszNCxSKmgkC%26pg%3DPA276%26dq%3DHitler%2527s%2BSecret%2BBook%2Bsparta%26ie%3DISO-8859-1%26sig%3Dq5g40V7M6bHFNX8pm4ZD65FxH6s%23PPA276%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Eugenics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
